* When changing folders or files, always check .github/workflows and apply the current folder structure to workflows
    * Update all scripts used for execution
    * Apply workflow using scripts
* Always test GitHub workflows locally before pushing
    * Use `act` tool to run workflows locally: `./scripts/test-workflow.sh` or `act -j <job-name>`
    * Verify workflow runs successfully locally before committing and pushing
* When database ORM is changed, always ensure updates can be applied

* Backend uses FastAPI
  * Apply good structure for FastAPI
    * Separate and manage route, endpoint, config, etc.
* Frontend is based on React + Vite and uses ShadCN UI.

* Agent should also be implemented by applying clean architecture, not implementing everything in one file